Business Brief -- Corning Inc.:
   Concern, Asahi Glass Agree
   To Pay Air Pollution Fine
Under terms of a consent decree, the companies also agreed
to use computers to monitor machinery that controls arsenic
emissions and to maintain the machinery at least once a year.
Corning Asahi supplies glass to television tube makers and
Corning Inc. is a glass, specialty materials and optical
fibers concern. Both are based in Corning, N.Y. Asahi Glass
is the U.S. unit of Tokyo's Asahi Glass Co.